context: Southeast Tucson continues to experience rapid residential development. The area includes <a5_0>Davis-Monthan Air Force Base<a5_0/>. The area is considered to be south of Golf Links Road. It is the home of <a4_0>Santa Rita High School<a4_0/>, Chuck Ford Park (<a6_0>Lakeside Park<a6_0/>), <a3_0>Lakeside Lake<a3_0/>, Lincoln Park (upper and lower), The Lakecrest Neighborhoods, and <a7_0>Pima Community College East Campus<a7_0/>. <a0_0>The Atterbury Wash<a0_0/> with its access to excellent bird watching is also located in the Southeast Tucson area. The suburban community of <a1_0><a8_0>Rita Ranch<a8_0/><a1_0/> houses many of the military families from Davis-Monthan, and is near the southeastern-most expansion of the current city limits. Close by Rita Ranch and also within the city limits lies <a2_0>Civano<a2_0/>, a planned development meant to <a9_0>showcase ecologically sound building practices and lifestyles<a9_0/>.
